description:
Hi,
I'm on the latest version of the develop/7 branch and I have an issue with this query:
INSERT {
    GRAPH ?g {
        ?s <http://data.linkedevents.org/def/location#businessType> <http://data.linkedevents.org/kos/3cixty/bar>
    }
} WHERE {
    GRAPH ?g {
        ?s <http://data.linkedevents.org/def/location#businessType> ?category .
    }
    FILTER (REGEX (STR (?category), "bars?$", "i")) .
    FILTER(NOT EXISTS{?s <http://data.linkedevents.org/def/location#businessType> <http://data.linkedevents.org/kos/3cixty/bar>}) .
}

Virtuoso give me this message and I don't see why:
-- More than 0 parameters, ignoring all the rest of the statement SPARQL INSERT {GRAPH ?g {?s <http://data.linkedevents.org/def/location#businessType> <http://data.linkedevents.org/kos/3cixty/bar>}} WHERE {    GRAPH ?g {?s <http://data.linkedevents.org/def/location#businessType> ?category .}FILTER (REGEX (STR (?category), "bars?$", "i")) .FILTER(NOT EXISTS{?s <http://data.linkedevents.org/def/location#businessType> <http://data.linkedevents.org/kos/3cixty/bar>}) .}
bin/isql: get_next_token: Unknown macro word ", " at line 13 of Top-Level

If it comes from my query, what is the problem ? Or if it comes from Virtuoso, why this message ?

